1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:03,295
I am Uhtred, son of Uhtred.

2
00:00:03,378 --> 00:00:07,257
Eardwulf has led the Danes
fo the greatest prize.

3
00:00:07,341 --> 00:00:11,762
After Tettenhall, Edward believes
the Danes no longer hold a threat.

4
00:00:11,845 --> 00:00:15,265
He's taken his army to Aegelesburg,
leaving Winchester undefended.

5
00:00:20,020 --> 00:00:23,649
But Sigtryggr sees the truth
of his dark heart.

6
00:00:23,732 --> 00:00:26,443
So, let this man's fate
serve as a warning.

7
00:00:28,904 --> 00:00:30,614
Haesten has entrapped me

8
00:00:30,697 --> 00:00:35,202
and I have lost those under my protection,
even my daughter Stiorra.

9
00:00:36,703 --> 00:00:39,414
And now the king's sons are held capfive.

10
00:00:39,498 --> 00:00:40,874
Don't let them kill us!

11
00:00:41,542 --> 00:00:43,585
Both my heirs!

12
00:00:43,669 --> 00:00:48,340
/In Edward's absence, the Danes
strengthen their grasp on Winchester.

13
00:00:48,423 --> 00:00:50,384
Lady Aelswith!

14
00:00:55,180 --> 00:00:57,933
Raise the Fyrd! Raise the Mercian Guard!

15
00:00:58,016 --> 00:01:02,062
7he king is rash
in his determination to retake the town

16
00:01:02,145 --> 00:01:04,314
and will not listen to reason.

17
00:01:04,398 --> 00:01:05,816
Do not do this!

18
00:01:05,899 --> 00:01:07,901
- Attack!
- No!

19
00:01:11,488 --> 00:01:13,407
Destiny is alll.

20
00:02:55,676 --> 00:02:59,137
- Has he gone mad?
- Leave him. He will not listen.

21
00:02:59,221 --> 00:03:02,516
- You must tell him he is being foolish.
- I have tried. He is not himself.

22
00:03:05,143 --> 00:03:08,230
Be kind, Uhtred. He is at heart
a boy who is suffering.

23
00:03:12,734 --> 00:03:14,653
Do you intend to set a fire?

24
00:03:14,736 --> 00:03:15,779
Yes.

25
00:03:16,363 --> 00:03:19,282
We encircle them and draw them out.

26
00:03:19,366 --> 00:03:21,118
Lord King, you should not do this.

27
00:03:21,201 --> 00:03:22,411
It is decided.

28
00:03:23,370 --> 00:03:25,789
The town walls cannot be breached
another way.

29
00:03:26,915 --> 00:03:29,042
Our attempts to attack have been futile.

30
00:03:29,584 --> 00:03:33,255
The Danes show no sign of surrender.
Perhaps this will force their hand.

31
00:03:33,338 --> 00:03:36,633
The fire will catch
and the town will be destroyed.

32
00:03:38,009 --> 00:03:40,637
Lord King, the heart of Wessex
will be burnt to ashes.

33
00:03:40,721 --> 00:03:44,558
And so the heathen burns in hell.
It is a risk I am resolved to.

34
00:03:44,641 --> 00:03:47,018
What are my choices, Uhtred? Surrender?

35
00:03:47,102 --> 00:03:49,896
Live in history as the King
who lost his lands?

36
00:03:49,980 --> 00:03:52,107
Thirty days we have tried and failed.

37
00:03:54,151 --> 00:03:58,822
I... I do this and in time Winchester will
rise again, stronger for her suffering.

38
00:03:58,905 --> 00:04:01,032
We should try again to speak
with Sigtryggr.

39
00:04:01,116 --> 00:04:03,243
This silence may be a sign
he looks for another way.

40
00:04:03,326 --> 00:04:05,036
They do not want to speak.

41
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:07,289
We send men. They send arrows.

42
00:04:07,372 --> 00:04:10,083
We have asked them to leave
and now our patience wears thin!

43
00:04:10,167 --> 00:04:13,587
Yes, and they will also be tired of this
and may be willing to negotiate.

44
00:04:13,670 --> 00:04:15,547
We are past negotiation.

45
00:04:15,630 --> 00:04:17,174
We win or they do!

46
00:04:17,257 --> 00:04:19,551
- Our families are prisoners...
- Aldhelm, what news?

47
00:04:22,262 --> 00:04:24,556
Lady Aethelflaed sent me here
to tell of a great victory.

48
00:04:25,724 --> 00:04:29,436
She has taken Eoferwic and the Danes there
have submitted to her rule.

49
00:04:29,519 --> 00:04:31,521
She now travels south with her army.

50
00:04:32,689 --> 00:04:36,943
Let her not be
shamed by weakness in her brother.

51
00:04:37,861 --> 00:04:41,740
Let her return to the land of her birth
and find it cleansed of the Danes.

52
00:04:42,407 --> 00:04:43,909
Tell them it is decided.

53
00:04:45,494 --> 00:04:48,580
If they do not surrender,
Winchester will burn!

54
00:05:35,126 --> 00:05:36,378
Formation!

55
00:05:37,629 --> 00:05:38,755
Halt!

56
00:05:54,938 --> 00:05:57,774
King Edward sends you
this message of intent!

57
00:06:01,945 --> 00:06:06,658
Leave the town, or on his command,
these flames will...

58
00:06:13,665 --> 00:06:15,584
I knew what he was going to say.

59
00:06:16,668 --> 00:06:17,794
They're getting desperate.

60
00:06:26,678 --> 00:06:30,682
"755, Cynewulf and the West Saxons

61
00:06:30,765 --> 00:06:36,229
deprived Sigebert of his kingdom,
because of his unlawful deeds.

62
00:06:36,771 --> 00:06:40,191
Cynewulf often fought
great battles in Wealas."

63
00:06:41,026 --> 00:06:45,030
Please, this is so dull.
I want to pull out my own eyes.

64
00:06:45,947 --> 00:06:47,782
Spoken like a true heathen.

65
00:06:49,910 --> 00:06:53,288
Shall we play another game?
What was the tally again?

66
00:06:53,371 --> 00:06:54,998
I am not keeping count.

67
00:06:55,540 --> 00:06:56,583
Come, read.

68
00:06:57,208 --> 00:06:58,877
I'm too hungry to read.

69
00:07:05,675 --> 00:07:09,095
- Is this the last of the bread?
- I am not keeping count of that either.

70
00:07:09,179 --> 00:07:10,722
Do you still have the grain?

71
00:07:16,436 --> 00:07:19,481
I'm taking the girl.
We need to kill a hostage.

72
00:07:20,273 --> 00:07:22,817
- And she will get their attention.
- They threaten to use fire.

73
00:07:22,901 --> 00:07:26,404
And in response, we show no mercy.

74
00:07:26,488 --> 00:07:28,949
Then not her. She is worthless.

75
00:07:29,032 --> 00:07:30,742
Not to the Dane-Slayer.

76
00:07:31,201 --> 00:07:34,454
Sigtryggr, I need Uhtred
to come out and fight.

77
00:07:34,537 --> 00:07:36,456
This will force his hand.

78
00:07:37,540 --> 00:07:39,876
Is this true? Will your father attack us?

79
00:07:39,960 --> 00:07:41,962
If he does, he'll destroy you.

80
00:07:43,672 --> 00:07:45,423
Do not succumb to anger, Brida.

81
00:07:45,507 --> 00:07:48,093
Haesten, tell the men
to get clay and water.

82
00:07:48,176 --> 00:07:50,762
Dampen the roofs.
Protect the walls from fire.

83
00:07:53,098 --> 00:07:55,225
Then I will select a hostage...

84
00:07:55,934 --> 00:07:57,560
and we will see what they do.

85
00:08:02,565 --> 00:08:04,985
Hurry up, men!

86
00:08:05,068 --> 00:08:06,194
Make haste!

87
00:08:09,114 --> 00:08:10,156
Take it.

88
00:08:28,466 --> 00:08:29,592
Here.

89
00:08:34,389 --> 00:08:36,725
There is some water in a flask here.

90
00:08:37,350 --> 00:08:39,436
But what are you doing?

91
00:08:40,186 --> 00:08:42,397
Don't worry. I will look after you.

92
00:08:53,033 --> 00:08:55,660
- Where is the water?
- You finished it.

93
00:08:55,744 --> 00:08:57,787
We must pray they offer more.

94
00:08:57,871 --> 00:09:00,415
- I am...
- Please do not say it again.

95
00:09:00,498 --> 00:09:01,750
We know you are hungry.

96
00:09:02,667 --> 00:09:05,587
She is not accustomed to discomfort.

97
00:09:05,670 --> 00:09:09,507
Discomfort! This is nothing compared
to what we endured in the marshland.

98
00:09:10,091 --> 00:09:11,885
Just be grateful there are no flies.

99
00:09:11,968 --> 00:09:14,721
I am grateful there is no screaming.

100
00:09:15,305 --> 00:09:18,058
I fear that is
because everyone is dead.

101
00:09:18,141 --> 00:09:22,437
We are being kept alive,
so they can make a show of our deaths.

102
00:09:22,979 --> 00:09:26,191
Then if they try to take me,
I shall throw myself upon their knives.

103
00:09:28,526 --> 00:09:31,279
I can show you a way
with a piece of cloth.

104
00:09:34,032 --> 00:09:37,243
I have learned things in my life,
which you do not know.

105
00:09:48,755 --> 00:09:52,592
There is a plant
that flowers in the courtyard.

106
00:09:53,968 --> 00:09:58,098
The purple blooms,
when dissolved in water, are tasteless...

107
00:09:59,307 --> 00:10:00,600
and effective...

108
00:10:01,059 --> 00:10:03,144
especially in children.

109
00:10:06,481 --> 00:10:08,983
Why would such a plant grow
in the courtyard?

110
00:10:11,736 --> 00:10:15,990
It was planted there,
should this situation ever arise.

111
00:10:35,927 --> 00:10:37,428
Give me the King's heir.

112
00:10:39,305 --> 00:10:42,851
- Come here, boy.
- No! That child is the King's first born.

113
00:10:42,934 --> 00:10:44,769
He does not care for my son. Take him.

114
00:10:45,395 --> 00:10:46,437
Foolish.

115
00:10:47,230 --> 00:10:50,942
He will assume you are lying
and take Aelfweard anyway.

116
00:10:51,901 --> 00:10:53,111
Are you lying?

117
00:10:56,573 --> 00:10:58,324
I do not know.

118
00:11:00,410 --> 00:11:03,413
Which of these two children
is more precious to his heart?

119
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:06,541
I'm the elder brother. I should be chosen.

120
00:11:11,379 --> 00:11:12,922
I will take them both.

121
00:11:25,894 --> 00:11:27,687
Do not give the signal.

122
00:11:27,770 --> 00:11:30,440
You must see how this plan
unleashes pointless slaughter.

123
00:11:30,523 --> 00:11:33,109
Each hour we wait is an insult
to my father!

124
00:11:33,193 --> 00:11:35,904
- Then think of the captives.
- They are lost to us!

125
00:11:36,613 --> 00:11:39,657
They were lost from the moment
the Danes arrived in Wessex.

126
00:11:39,741 --> 00:11:41,117
Do you not see it?

127
00:11:41,201 --> 00:11:42,785
This is my punishment.

128
00:11:42,869 --> 00:11:45,246
I abandoned the children of Mercia

129
00:11:45,330 --> 00:11:47,457
and this is God's vengeance
for that mistake.

130
00:11:47,540 --> 00:11:49,209
God would not do that, Lord.

131
00:11:49,292 --> 00:11:51,461
We do not have to burn Winchester!

132
00:11:52,003 --> 00:11:54,130
I swear to you I will find another way.

133
00:11:55,089 --> 00:11:57,634
And you always keep to your word, Uhtred.

134
00:12:02,347 --> 00:12:05,225
I will get in, find this Sigtryggr and...

135
00:12:05,308 --> 00:12:08,394
How? We built those walls
never to be breached.

136
00:12:08,478 --> 00:12:10,730
So far, they've been
more steadfast than any of us.

137
00:12:10,813 --> 00:12:12,106
Father!

138
00:12:13,274 --> 00:12:14,484
Uhtred?

139
00:12:16,527 --> 00:12:18,655
- What are you doing here?
- Where is she?

140
00:12:20,865 --> 00:12:22,158
Where is Stiorra?

141
00:12:22,242 --> 00:12:24,702
She is within,
but we have a plan to save her.

142
00:12:28,289 --> 00:12:31,000
King Edward of Wessex!

143
00:12:34,128 --> 00:12:35,338
Make ready.

144
00:12:36,506 --> 00:12:39,550
King Edward of Wessex!

145
00:12:40,093 --> 00:12:43,638
I have shown myself. Do the same.

146
00:12:47,767 --> 00:12:51,854
Approach the gate
and meet me face to face!

147
00:12:53,064 --> 00:12:56,442
I will not take orders from a Dane.

148
00:12:57,443 --> 00:13:00,697
Let us talk, eye to eye!

149
00:13:00,780 --> 00:13:03,491
This is a game and I will not play.

150
00:13:04,492 --> 00:13:08,788
Tell him to surrender, or I will give
the signal to burn them all.

151
00:13:11,833 --> 00:13:12,917
Bring the boys.

152
00:13:19,048 --> 00:13:20,133
Lord King!

153
00:13:32,895 --> 00:13:34,772
Lower your weapons!

154
00:13:37,734 --> 00:13:39,152
Come!

155
00:13:39,235 --> 00:13:41,988
Talk to us at the gate!

156
00:13:46,534 --> 00:13:47,660
Come now!

157
00:13:48,411 --> 00:13:50,413
Your sons want to see their father!

158
00:13:53,624 --> 00:13:56,210
Lord, do not approach the gate.

159
00:14:22,320 --> 00:14:27,367
Give me my children,
or I will find yours and take their eyes.

160
00:14:27,450 --> 00:14:29,202
I have no children.

161
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:31,954
Nor a wife.

162
00:14:32,914 --> 00:14:34,832
This is why I'm stronger than you.

163
00:14:36,501 --> 00:14:37,960
Give me my children!

164
00:14:39,879 --> 00:14:41,672
I command it.

165
00:14:44,050 --> 00:14:47,595
I will give you
one of your sons if you retreat.

166
00:14:47,678 --> 00:14:49,514
And you may choose which.

167
00:15:21,921 --> 00:15:23,089
Someone speak.

168
00:15:25,133 --> 00:15:26,717
What do I do?

169
00:15:29,887 --> 00:15:31,347
Request the aetheling.

170
00:15:31,931 --> 00:15:35,435
If I choose one child,
what happens to the other...

171
00:15:35,518 --> 00:15:37,687
It is a hard decision, yes.

172
00:15:37,770 --> 00:15:42,191
But I think it is part of a longer
strategy to see if you will negotiate.

173
00:15:42,275 --> 00:15:46,529
I... I have looked that man in the eye
and he is not one to give ground.

174
00:15:50,408 --> 00:15:51,659
What do you think?

175
00:15:54,704 --> 00:15:56,539
That if we show weakness now...

176
00:15:57,665 --> 00:16:00,418
he will make a show of cruelty.

177
00:16:01,627 --> 00:16:03,129
I think say nothing.

178
00:16:04,797 --> 00:16:05,923
Can we pay him?

179
00:16:06,716 --> 00:16:09,760
He doesn't want silver.
If he did, he would have taken it...

180
00:16:09,844 --> 00:16:12,221
He wants to destroy us
and destroy our spirit.

181
00:16:17,477 --> 00:16:19,854
I cannot do this. I can...

182
00:16:20,813 --> 00:16:24,775
I can... I cannot... I cannot.
I cannot do this.

183
00:16:31,407 --> 00:16:32,742
What would you do?

184
00:16:38,039 --> 00:16:39,540
Much the same as him.

185
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:42,335
Be broken by it.

186
00:16:42,877 --> 00:16:44,587
Any man would.

187
00:16:44,670 --> 00:16:47,381
It is unnatural to have to choose
between your children.

188
00:16:47,465 --> 00:16:49,133
I would want you to pick Stiorra.

189
00:16:49,842 --> 00:16:52,011
I could defend myself
if it happened to us.

190
00:16:52,094 --> 00:16:53,763
It will not happen to us.

191
00:16:55,431 --> 00:16:57,391
And it will not happen to the King.

192
00:16:59,310 --> 00:17:01,562
Are you going to do something foolish?

193
00:17:01,646 --> 00:17:03,064
Are you going to stop me?

194
00:17:09,612 --> 00:17:11,614
Then you should be pragmatic...

195
00:17:12,448 --> 00:17:14,992
and choose the son
whose legitimacy is not in question.

196
00:17:15,076 --> 00:17:18,329
I cannot. I cannot be the man
to condemn one son over the other.

197
00:17:19,288 --> 00:17:21,165
There must be something else he wants.

198
00:17:21,249 --> 00:17:22,500
He wants me dead.

199
00:17:25,670 --> 00:17:27,630
This much I know from Haesten.

200
00:17:29,257 --> 00:17:31,133
He would not trade you for my sons.

201
00:17:31,217 --> 00:17:34,178
You... You are not
that valuable to me, Uhtred.

202
00:17:35,596 --> 00:17:36,639
True.

203
00:17:37,807 --> 00:17:39,725
But I do have a value to the Danes.

204
00:17:40,226 --> 00:17:43,271
To kill the man they call the Dane-Slayer
would bring great reputation.

205
00:17:43,354 --> 00:17:44,564
He might want that.

206
00:17:45,731 --> 00:17:49,193
And Brida will want revenge
for her enslavement in Wealas.

207
00:17:49,277 --> 00:17:51,487
Let me offer myself. It is worth trying.

208
00:17:58,828 --> 00:18:01,497
Then Wessex would once again
be in your debt.

209
00:18:08,004 --> 00:18:13,801
And should you not return, I will ensure
they speak of your honor through the ages.

210
00:18:14,802 --> 00:18:16,929
Uhtred will not be forgotten.

211
00:18:20,474 --> 00:18:21,726
This is a brave plan.

212
00:18:22,602 --> 00:18:23,686
Which plan is that?

213
00:18:23,769 --> 00:18:25,021
He doesn't have a plan.

214
00:18:25,104 --> 00:18:27,315
This is what he looks like
when he's making it up.

215
00:18:27,398 --> 00:18:29,198
You cannot hope to take them
on single-handed?

216
00:18:29,275 --> 00:18:31,152
What do you think he's doing, then?

217
00:18:31,235 --> 00:18:33,195
I presume you're trying
to get us some time.

218
00:18:34,030 --> 00:18:36,311
If you can delay the Danes
until Lady Aethelflaed arrives,

219
00:18:36,365 --> 00:18:39,118
she will persuade Edward
to endure a longer siege.

220
00:18:39,201 --> 00:18:42,163
You know that we can take back the town
when they're depleted.

221
00:18:42,663 --> 00:18:45,625
- That is not my plan, Aldhelm.
- Ha! Told you.

222
00:18:46,375 --> 00:18:48,628
Why else would you make
such a dangerous offer?

223
00:18:51,756 --> 00:18:53,633
Because I believe I can end this.

224
00:19:21,827 --> 00:19:23,120
Sigtryggr!

225
00:19:25,581 --> 00:19:26,957
Show yourself!

226
00:19:30,127 --> 00:19:31,796
But I killed him...

227
00:19:31,879 --> 00:19:33,172
What?

228
00:19:33,255 --> 00:19:34,507
We...

229
00:19:34,590 --> 00:19:36,258
We have tried to kill him.

230
00:19:38,010 --> 00:19:40,137
And yet here he is...

231
00:19:41,013 --> 00:19:44,433
returned from the dead,
like their nailed god.

232
00:19:46,102 --> 00:19:48,187
And not for the first time, I hear.

233
00:19:50,189 --> 00:19:53,317
I have learned a lot about him
from his daughter.

234
00:19:54,610 --> 00:19:56,862
We will not retreat, Sigtryggr!

235
00:19:57,446 --> 00:19:59,031
Instead, we make you this offer.

236
00:19:59,115 --> 00:20:01,492
Send out both the children...

237
00:20:02,076 --> 00:20:05,913
and I will walk into Winchester alone.

238
00:20:08,582 --> 00:20:11,627
And why would I
exchange gold for silver?

239
00:20:12,545 --> 00:20:15,715
Because you will have
the Saxons' greatest warrior!

240
00:20:18,050 --> 00:20:21,178
And because you know that,
in time, I would kill you...

241
00:20:21,262 --> 00:20:23,806
as I have killed your friends
and your brothers.

242
00:20:24,515 --> 00:20:25,766
Is he lying?

243
00:20:27,101 --> 00:20:28,144
No.

244
00:20:30,479 --> 00:20:32,022
What his daughter said is true.

245
00:20:33,107 --> 00:20:35,359
We cannot conquer this place
while he lives.

246
00:20:38,154 --> 00:20:39,989
Edward can make other heirs.

247
00:20:40,531 --> 00:20:42,575
He cannot make another Uhtred.

248
00:20:47,997 --> 00:20:50,541
Then perhaps we should tear him to pieces.

249
00:20:53,085 --> 00:20:54,462
Make the exchange.

250
00:20:54,486 --> 00:21:02,486
http://hiqve.com/

251
00:22:37,857 --> 00:22:39,233
How long do we give him?

252
00:22:41,986 --> 00:22:43,195
As long as he needs.

253
00:22:47,283 --> 00:22:48,784
We'll know when the time comes.

254
00:23:12,766 --> 00:23:15,644
Your king could not choose
between his sons.

255
00:23:20,900 --> 00:23:22,067
And so...

256
00:23:22,985 --> 00:23:25,112
Guards, bring in the prisoner!

257
00:23:27,406 --> 00:23:32,036
He has given us his greatest warrior
in their place!

258
00:23:40,920 --> 00:23:42,046
Bring him to me.

259
00:23:55,309 --> 00:23:57,645
I did not know about the child.

260
00:24:00,230 --> 00:24:01,565
Neither did Cnut.

261
00:24:04,610 --> 00:24:08,364
All will be avenged when you suffer
as I have suffered.

262
00:24:09,531 --> 00:24:12,451
Tie him to the crucifix
in the marketplace!

263
00:24:12,993 --> 00:24:16,372
Let him die like the Christian
he tries to be!

264
00:24:18,582 --> 00:24:20,668
In time, Brida.

265
00:24:20,751 --> 00:24:24,213
- Take him to the hall.
- What? Sigtryggr...

266
00:24:24,296 --> 00:24:27,007
Sigtryggr! We agreed.

267
00:24:27,841 --> 00:24:31,011
I swear that you shall have him
when I am finished with him.

268
00:24:31,804 --> 00:24:32,888
On my honor.

269
00:24:34,056 --> 00:24:35,099
His sword.

270
00:24:41,522 --> 00:24:44,441
Return the captives to the chapel
and feed them.

271
00:24:44,525 --> 00:24:46,151
I need them alive...

272
00:24:47,736 --> 00:24:49,029
for now.

273
00:24:51,365 --> 00:24:52,908
Do you like this?

274
00:24:54,868 --> 00:24:56,161
Then I need your help.

275
00:24:56,870 --> 00:24:59,373
I don't want his sword!
I want him!

276
00:24:59,456 --> 00:25:02,167
- You'll have your revenge, Brida.
- Sigtryggr!

277
00:25:26,984 --> 00:25:28,777
What does this mean?

278
00:25:29,278 --> 00:25:31,030
Why this sudden kindness?

279
00:25:31,113 --> 00:25:33,073
Sigtryggr toys with us.

280
00:25:33,157 --> 00:25:36,285
Whether it means a reprieve,
I do not know.

281
00:25:36,368 --> 00:25:39,371
Well, the children are safe.

282
00:25:39,455 --> 00:25:40,664
That is enough for now.

283
00:25:41,832 --> 00:25:44,251
Let us break bread and be thankful.

284
00:25:49,089 --> 00:25:51,633
Drink enough water,
then give me back the jug.

285
00:25:51,717 --> 00:25:53,802
After that point, do not drink anymore.

286
00:25:55,345 --> 00:25:56,388
Why?

287
00:25:57,389 --> 00:25:59,933
If the King cannot choose
between his sons,

288
00:26:00,017 --> 00:26:01,727
it may be that we need to ensure

289
00:26:01,810 --> 00:26:05,856
Aethelstan does not have
a powerful friend.

290
00:26:34,968 --> 00:26:36,762
You are fast.

291
00:26:36,845 --> 00:26:38,514
I think you are not trying.

292
00:26:38,597 --> 00:26:42,017
Why would I not try? When you are
the killer of so many of my kin?

293
00:26:42,101 --> 00:26:44,603
That is a question only you can answer.

294
00:26:48,774 --> 00:26:51,777
Perhaps your reputation is exaggerated.

295
00:26:54,822 --> 00:26:56,907
I've been reading his chronicle.

296
00:26:59,201 --> 00:27:00,661
You are not in it.

297
00:27:02,246 --> 00:27:05,749
Alfred did not want it known
how much he owed to a heathen.

298
00:27:08,127 --> 00:27:12,131
If you are not of their God,
then why do you choose them?

299
00:27:14,675 --> 00:27:17,427
- They are my people.
- And they accept you as such?

300
00:27:17,511 --> 00:27:19,304
Many heathens live here in peace.

301
00:27:19,388 --> 00:27:21,515
It is only the Kings
who cannot find accord.

302
00:27:24,017 --> 00:27:25,102
Interesting.

303
00:27:26,061 --> 00:27:28,188
Your daughter, she said the same.

304
00:27:29,022 --> 00:27:30,065
Where is she?

305
00:27:30,149 --> 00:27:31,483
She is here.

306
00:27:32,234 --> 00:27:33,944
She's been well-treated.

307
00:27:35,237 --> 00:27:38,490
Hm, I see the Dane in her.

308
00:27:40,617 --> 00:27:43,453
She has not been dishonored,
I swear to that.

309
00:27:44,246 --> 00:27:48,584
No, your daughter is
a very intelligent young woman...

310
00:27:49,126 --> 00:27:51,420
which she apparently gets from her mother.

311
00:27:51,503 --> 00:27:53,338
We've talked a great deal.

312
00:27:54,798 --> 00:27:56,633
She has told me much about you...

313
00:27:57,092 --> 00:28:00,012
how you fought for peace in Mercia...

314
00:28:00,387 --> 00:28:03,182
how you gave up the woman you loved.

315
00:28:03,265 --> 00:28:09,688
But my favorite tale was how
you lost your home at Bebbanburg.

316
00:28:09,771 --> 00:28:11,231
Why is that of interest?

317
00:28:11,315 --> 00:28:13,442
Because I too have lost a home.

318
00:28:15,068 --> 00:28:20,490
And, so, I wonder if that puts us
on common ground.

319
00:28:26,747 --> 00:28:28,290
Do you wish to strike a bargain?

320
00:28:29,917 --> 00:28:31,793
Is that why you have not killed me?

321
00:28:33,837 --> 00:28:35,380
Why not approach the King?

322
00:28:35,464 --> 00:28:40,719
Because the King is not a decisive man
and men like that, they cannot negotiate.

323
00:28:40,802 --> 00:28:45,432
You, on the other hand, you offered
your lover to preserve a kingdom.

324
00:28:45,515 --> 00:28:48,268
So, I presume you can
make difficult choices.

325
00:28:51,813 --> 00:28:55,275
- But I have nothing to give.
- But you have influence with those who do.

326
00:28:57,611 --> 00:28:59,279
And they follow you.

327
00:29:01,615 --> 00:29:03,158
What is it you want?

328
00:29:03,242 --> 00:29:04,284
Peace.

329
00:29:05,202 --> 00:29:07,120
Or peace and land.

330
00:29:07,204 --> 00:29:10,082
And you try to find peace
by starting a war?

331
00:29:11,583 --> 00:29:12,918
Where is the battle?

332
00:29:14,461 --> 00:29:16,129
Where is the war?

333
00:29:18,882 --> 00:29:21,093
I guessed you wanted to negotiate.

334
00:29:21,802 --> 00:29:23,637
The king would not believe it.

335
00:29:23,720 --> 00:29:26,848
Who told you that I would be willing
to strike a bargain?

336
00:29:26,932 --> 00:29:28,934
Oh, you did...

337
00:29:30,185 --> 00:29:32,271
when you chose to enter the town.

338
00:29:34,189 --> 00:29:36,316
The offer had been made.

339
00:29:36,942 --> 00:29:39,987
All we have to do is get Edward
to agree to a meeting...

340
00:29:40,070 --> 00:29:41,613
and argue the terms.

341
00:29:42,698 --> 00:29:44,866
Haesten! Are you spying on them?

342
00:29:47,160 --> 00:29:48,704
I spy on everyone.

343
00:29:50,455 --> 00:29:51,957
What is he doing with him?

344
00:29:52,040 --> 00:29:53,625
I fear to tell you.

345
00:29:53,709 --> 00:29:55,627
Haesten, what's happening in there?

346
00:29:59,506 --> 00:30:00,590
You should know...

347
00:30:01,383 --> 00:30:03,135
Sigtryggr seeks a truce.

348
00:30:06,179 --> 00:30:08,307
That is a good thing, Brida.

349
00:30:08,390 --> 00:30:10,267
It means more land, more silver.

350
00:30:13,979 --> 00:30:15,355
It means betrayal.

351
00:30:15,439 --> 00:30:17,065
You are foolish.

352
00:30:19,735 --> 00:30:20,944
This could soon be over.

353
00:30:25,574 --> 00:30:26,908
Cowards.

354
00:30:26,992 --> 00:30:28,910
Liars and cowards all of you!

355
00:30:29,828 --> 00:30:33,248
Go in the north. You need good weather
to go through there.

356
00:30:33,332 --> 00:30:35,000
Why don't you go up to Eoferwic?

357
00:31:04,154 --> 00:31:08,325
Well, I don't think this is going to work.

358
00:32:16,685 --> 00:32:19,771
Do not lose faith.
He will have survived.

359
00:32:26,486 --> 00:32:27,529
Lord.

360
00:32:28,780 --> 00:32:31,199
No, I'm begging, Lord King,
just give him more time.

361
00:32:31,283 --> 00:32:33,660
Do not attack whilst he is within.
Please, Lord.

362
00:32:33,743 --> 00:32:35,871
- This does not mean the end.
- My Lord.

363
00:32:35,954 --> 00:32:38,623
Lord King, we have followed
Uhtred for years.

364
00:32:38,707 --> 00:32:39,875
He's never failed!

365
00:32:39,958 --> 00:32:42,127
He never failed
because good men followed him.

366
00:32:45,172 --> 00:32:47,757
But even he could not
take on an army alone.

367
00:32:47,841 --> 00:32:49,259
It was unwise.

368
00:32:49,926 --> 00:32:55,140
It is painful to speak it, but your Lord
has lost a battle he could never win.

369
00:33:00,770 --> 00:33:02,189
There is no hope for him.

370
00:33:31,843 --> 00:33:34,596
Lord King!
Our scouts send good news!

371
00:33:35,931 --> 00:33:38,475
The Lady of Mercia has come.
She brings an army!

372
00:33:48,193 --> 00:33:50,946
The King is trying to be bold,
but his decisions are rash.

373
00:33:51,029 --> 00:33:54,366
I'm certain that with more time,
the siege can be ended without slaughter.

374
00:33:54,449 --> 00:33:56,576
Edward, I have heard the boys
have been freed.

375
00:33:56,660 --> 00:34:00,747
One mercy has been shown, yes.
I hear Danes have submitted in the north.

376
00:34:00,830 --> 00:34:03,959
Yes. And what has been done once
can be done twice.

377
00:34:04,042 --> 00:34:07,671
If you have your sons, you have everything
you need for Alfred's line to thrive.

378
00:34:08,380 --> 00:34:11,424
Walls can be rebuilt, palaces, even tombs.

379
00:34:12,300 --> 00:34:14,135
Edward, you are Wessex.

380
00:34:14,219 --> 00:34:16,972
Whatever you decide,
Mercia will support you.

381
00:34:18,390 --> 00:34:21,643
He cannot lose Winchester.
It would rip out our father's heart.

382
00:34:21,726 --> 00:34:23,766
We should not put that above
the lives of innocents.

383
00:34:23,812 --> 00:34:26,690
- No, Aethelflaed is right.
- How many people are within?

384
00:34:26,773 --> 00:34:29,401
Many. And there are those, of course,
inside of royal blood,

385
00:34:29,484 --> 00:34:30,819
my wife, our mother.

386
00:34:31,361 --> 00:34:33,613
Mother would not want you to capitulate.

387
00:34:33,697 --> 00:34:36,658
She is by Father's side
and will be reconciled to dying.

388
00:34:36,741 --> 00:34:39,828
Then we shall proceed,
but not as they expect.

389
00:34:39,911 --> 00:34:45,667
They have made provisions against fire,
so, let us use smoke to conceal an attack.

390
00:34:45,750 --> 00:34:47,460
If God and the winds are in our favor,

391
00:34:47,544 --> 00:34:50,314
it will choke those guarding the gates
and allow us to breach the walls.

392
00:34:50,338 --> 00:34:53,091
But if the wind turns,
then we ourselves are smothered.

393
00:34:53,174 --> 00:34:54,384
Lady, I beg you.

394
00:34:54,467 --> 00:34:57,095
- Give Lord Uhtred more time.
- Lord Uhtred is already dead.

395
00:35:06,104 --> 00:35:08,773
Dead or alive, it does not matter.

396
00:35:09,858 --> 00:35:14,321
We cannot hand Winchester
over to the Danes for the life of one man.

397
00:35:14,404 --> 00:35:15,739
Indeed.

398
00:35:15,822 --> 00:35:18,617
Set the hay sacks close to the gates.

399
00:35:18,700 --> 00:35:22,203
Add shit and lime,
so they may choke on the stench.

400
00:35:22,287 --> 00:35:25,165
We force men from the ramparts
and into the streets,

401
00:35:25,248 --> 00:35:27,334
breach the gates and slaughter them!

402
00:36:40,990 --> 00:36:42,200
Here.

403
00:36:44,661 --> 00:36:45,870
Are you leaving?

404
00:36:45,954 --> 00:36:46,996
Yes.

405
00:36:47,914 --> 00:36:51,418
They are at the gates and I do not want
to be here for the fight.

406
00:36:52,961 --> 00:36:57,048
- And you are coming with me.
- No. No, no, I cannot.

407
00:37:00,844 --> 00:37:03,805
They will be slaughtered!

408
00:37:08,435 --> 00:37:09,519
Come with me.

409
00:37:10,395 --> 00:37:13,815
Many women have grown to appreciate
my charms, given a year or so.

410
00:37:32,333 --> 00:37:33,460
Get back!

411
00:37:51,227 --> 00:37:52,270
Down there.

412
00:37:54,689 --> 00:37:56,649
- Will we get out?
- Yes!

413
00:37:56,733 --> 00:37:58,735
Save yourself from what will follow.

414
00:37:58,818 --> 00:37:59,861
No!

415
00:37:59,944 --> 00:38:01,780
You will not survive the fight!

416
00:38:01,863 --> 00:38:03,531
We have no time for this!

417
00:38:03,615 --> 00:38:04,991
Stay and you die!

418
00:38:05,074 --> 00:38:06,743
My place is with the captives!

419
00:38:06,826 --> 00:38:09,662
Ah, die, then, ungrateful bitch!

420
00:38:16,461 --> 00:38:18,129
Edward has attacked us.

421
00:38:18,213 --> 00:38:19,339
Come with me.

422
00:38:21,716 --> 00:38:22,759
Uhtred.

423
00:38:23,885 --> 00:38:26,429
You betray me, all will suffer.

424
00:38:45,114 --> 00:38:46,449
Quickly! Get back!

425
00:38:53,414 --> 00:38:55,250
One formation!

426
00:39:25,989 --> 00:39:29,200
Pull back! Protect your men! Keep tight!

427
00:40:20,793 --> 00:40:24,339
Let me speak with him.
Let me speak with the King.

428
00:40:24,422 --> 00:40:28,134
Go with this man.
If he kills Danes, kill him.

429
00:40:54,369 --> 00:40:56,287
Stand down your men!

430
00:40:56,371 --> 00:40:58,790
Edward, stand down!

431
00:40:58,873 --> 00:41:00,166
Stand down!

432
00:41:14,931 --> 00:41:16,182
Edward!

433
00:41:17,934 --> 00:41:19,936
Edward! Edward!

434
00:41:22,355 --> 00:41:26,693
Lord, you must trust me! I spoke to him.

435
00:41:26,776 --> 00:41:28,903
Edward, stop this fight!

436
00:41:34,367 --> 00:41:36,411
- It's too late!
- Trust me!

437
00:41:36,494 --> 00:41:39,539
Sigtryggr is willing to negotiate!
Why would I lie to you?

438
00:41:39,622 --> 00:41:41,833
I have spoken to him. He will stand down!

439
00:41:41,916 --> 00:41:43,543
Winchester is going to burn!

440
00:41:43,626 --> 00:41:47,296
Sigtryggr! Stand down your men!

441
00:41:47,380 --> 00:41:49,799
Order the shield wall! Do it now!

442
00:41:53,011 --> 00:41:55,596
Did you get what you came for?

443
00:41:55,680 --> 00:41:58,683
Sigtryggr! Stand down your men!

444
00:42:02,103 --> 00:42:04,188
You can get what you came for!

445
00:42:06,858 --> 00:42:09,318
Shield wall!

446
00:42:18,619 --> 00:42:21,956
Shield wall!

447
00:42:25,543 --> 00:42:30,256
Shield wall!

448
00:42:40,558 --> 00:42:41,809
Get back!

449
00:42:42,518 --> 00:42:44,645
Hold the line! Back!

450
00:42:45,313 --> 00:42:47,273
- Dear God!
- Stay back!

451
00:42:47,774 --> 00:42:48,858
Please.

452
00:42:52,862 --> 00:42:54,864
Eadith. Eadith.

453
00:42:54,947 --> 00:42:56,074
Stay back.

454
00:42:56,157 --> 00:42:57,909
Finan!

455
00:42:57,992 --> 00:43:00,203
She's all right. Come on.

456
00:43:00,286 --> 00:43:01,329
Move!

457
00:43:02,371 --> 00:43:05,374
- Get back! Get back!
- Move!

458
00:43:06,751 --> 00:43:10,880
- Hold the line! Hold the lines!
- You heard him!

459
00:43:25,394 --> 00:43:29,023
Sigtryggr, you wish to talk with us?

460
00:43:30,191 --> 00:43:33,444
There will be no negotiation
until we see the captives.

461
00:43:37,657 --> 00:43:38,741
Welcome.

462
00:44:19,407 --> 00:44:22,869
Uhtred tells me you have gone north.

463
00:44:24,620 --> 00:44:27,623
I want Eoferwic
and the lands that surround it.

464
00:44:27,707 --> 00:44:31,502
- No, we have just recaptured Eoferwic.
- Which is why I want it.

465
00:44:31,586 --> 00:44:33,880
For decades, we have fought
to push Danes from there.

466
00:44:33,963 --> 00:44:36,716
To give it to you
would set us back a generation.

467
00:44:36,799 --> 00:44:38,634
Then I will keep Winchester.

468
00:44:40,761 --> 00:44:42,346
We can offer you East Anglia.

469
00:44:42,430 --> 00:44:46,058
It is bigger and has access
to your homeland from the sea.

470
00:44:46,142 --> 00:44:47,768
I want Eoferwic.

471
00:44:47,852 --> 00:44:49,270
I cannot agree.

472
00:44:49,353 --> 00:44:51,480
It is unclear
what your choices are.

473
00:44:58,112 --> 00:45:01,699
- Perhaps we should consider it.
- He would be on my border!

474
00:45:02,783 --> 00:45:05,119
Edward, do not let him divide us.

475
00:45:05,203 --> 00:45:07,872
I will leave you to trade
between yourselves.

476
00:45:07,955 --> 00:45:09,415
I'll find my daughter.

477
00:45:28,517 --> 00:45:30,102
Did you think I would forget you?

478
00:45:30,186 --> 00:45:31,771
Stop this! It is over.

479
00:45:31,854 --> 00:45:33,356
It is never over.

480
00:45:35,942 --> 00:45:38,736
Brida! I spared your life!

481
00:45:38,819 --> 00:45:40,738
You destroyed my life!

482
00:45:40,821 --> 00:45:42,907
You know nothing of how I suffered!

483
00:45:42,990 --> 00:45:45,451
I will not kill you, nor Cnut's child.

484
00:45:45,534 --> 00:45:48,788
He is not Cnut's. He is mine alone!

485
00:45:48,871 --> 00:45:52,416
And he will be loyal to me,
as no man ever has!

486
00:45:52,500 --> 00:45:55,378
I will breed in him
a hatred of all Saxons.

487
00:45:55,461 --> 00:45:59,048
Then you condemn your child
to a bloody death and that will undo you!

488
00:46:09,558 --> 00:46:11,227
Fight on and they will kill you!

489
00:46:13,479 --> 00:46:16,023
If not the Saxon kings,
then Sigtryggr himself.

490
00:46:16,107 --> 00:46:18,234
But I am not afraid of that.

491
00:46:19,068 --> 00:46:21,279
I have not lost faith in what comes after.

492
00:46:21,821 --> 00:46:22,989
Do it!

493
00:46:24,365 --> 00:46:25,574
Do it!

494
00:46:25,658 --> 00:46:26,867
Kill me.

495
00:46:28,119 --> 00:46:30,454
If you do not, I will become stronger.

496
00:46:32,832 --> 00:46:35,167
Blood has been shed. More will flow.

497
00:46:35,918 --> 00:46:38,671
I will take revenge on all of those
who have betrayed me

498
00:46:38,754 --> 00:46:41,966
and I will not rest
until they suffer at my hand.

499
00:46:43,926 --> 00:46:45,678
Do it!

500
00:46:49,682 --> 00:46:51,183
Or I will be your undoing.

501
00:47:00,609 --> 00:47:01,694
Just leave.

502
00:47:03,321 --> 00:47:04,613
Have your child.

503
00:47:07,325 --> 00:47:08,909
Leave while you can.

504
00:47:21,839 --> 00:47:23,758
I never know where she is.

505
00:47:23,841 --> 00:47:25,217
Careful, Osferth!

506
00:47:32,308 --> 00:47:33,517
Have you struck a bargain?

507
00:47:36,354 --> 00:47:38,647
He... He will take Eoferwic...

508
00:47:39,273 --> 00:47:42,526
and agree never to enter Wessex,
Mercia or East Anglia.

509
00:47:42,610 --> 00:47:44,862
So, you hold three of the four Kingdoms.

510
00:47:46,155 --> 00:47:47,740
That is no humiliation.

511
00:47:51,452 --> 00:47:54,330
Sigtryggr would like to take
one of the captives.

512
00:47:58,042 --> 00:47:59,126
Your daughter.

513
00:48:01,796 --> 00:48:03,422
Which you have refused.

514
00:48:06,258 --> 00:48:09,595
Because you know what it is
to have your child used in a bargain!

515
00:48:11,055 --> 00:48:12,973
Stiorra is not a child.

516
00:48:14,892 --> 00:48:16,310
She is a young woman.

517
00:48:19,397 --> 00:48:21,315
So, we did not refuse.

518
00:48:44,964 --> 00:48:46,382
I thought I'd lost you.

519
00:48:50,719 --> 00:48:51,846
I'll miss you.

520
00:48:56,851 --> 00:48:57,935
Why?

521
00:48:58,769 --> 00:48:59,937
When I leave.

522
00:49:01,147 --> 00:49:02,356
I have said no.

523
00:49:04,442 --> 00:49:06,986
But I'm... I'm willing to go.

524
00:49:08,612 --> 00:49:09,738
With Sigtryggr?

525
00:49:11,615 --> 00:49:15,619
- But I want you with me in Coccham.
- There's nothing for me in Coccham.

526
00:49:15,703 --> 00:49:17,872
It's the chance for us to be one family.

527
00:49:17,955 --> 00:49:20,708
It's not what either of us wants.

528
00:49:20,791 --> 00:49:24,503
You'd like it to be true, but it's not.
Your men are your family.

529
00:49:24,962 --> 00:49:27,006
I want my children with me.

530
00:49:27,089 --> 00:49:28,424
Maybe in Bebbanburg.

531
00:49:28,507 --> 00:49:32,344
Maybe then, but you're not destined
to be the Lord of Coccham

532
00:49:32,428 --> 00:49:35,264
any more than I'm meant to live
a small life there.

533
00:49:36,265 --> 00:49:37,475
We're wanderers, Father.

534
00:49:37,558 --> 00:49:41,145
We follow where the gods lead us
and the gods are sending me to Daneland.

535
00:49:41,896 --> 00:49:45,858
Let me go...
for the sake of all Saxons.

536
00:49:46,692 --> 00:49:50,488
- I have sacrificed enough for them.
- Well, I have sacrificed nothing.

537
00:49:51,906 --> 00:49:55,701
Please! I want to live
amongst my mother's people,

538
00:49:55,784 --> 00:50:00,956
to find the part of myself that died
when she was taken from me.

539
00:50:08,547 --> 00:50:09,632
Besides...

540
00:50:12,510 --> 00:50:14,136
Sigtryggr is gentle.

541
00:50:17,181 --> 00:50:18,849
He's a man of honor!

542
00:50:33,864 --> 00:50:35,699
You are mine to take care of.

543
00:50:36,659 --> 00:50:39,286
For too long, you've had nothing from me.

544
00:50:39,370 --> 00:50:41,914
I've had everything from you.

545
00:50:43,499 --> 00:50:47,211
Your blood is within me
and it's made me a restless spirit.

546
00:50:47,294 --> 00:50:49,463
Please give me this chance
to live as you do,

547
00:50:50,172 --> 00:50:53,467
to follow a path without having certainty
of where it's going to end.

548
00:50:57,346 --> 00:50:58,514
Let me go.

549
00:51:03,894 --> 00:51:05,688
How did you like your first battle?

550
00:51:07,106 --> 00:51:08,983
I swear it will be my last.

551
00:51:10,276 --> 00:51:12,653
From now on,
I will be staying in the tent.

552
00:51:14,363 --> 00:51:16,532
You showed the spirit of a true warrior.

553
00:51:18,117 --> 00:51:20,703
Perhaps my family honor is restored.

554
00:51:21,870 --> 00:51:24,790
If only those who cared for me
were still here to see it.

555
00:51:36,176 --> 00:51:39,555
Rest. It is over.

556
00:51:49,189 --> 00:51:51,025
Mother!

557
00:51:51,567 --> 00:51:52,776
Mother!

558
00:51:55,988 --> 00:51:57,156
Mother!

559
00:52:06,457 --> 00:52:07,833
My mother is taken ill.

560
00:52:07,916 --> 00:52:10,377
I fear the Danes have claimed
another life.

561
00:52:11,086 --> 00:52:12,755
She's strong.

562
00:52:17,468 --> 00:52:19,219
My mother cannot care for him.

563
00:52:20,429 --> 00:52:21,680
How could I?

564
00:52:21,764 --> 00:52:24,475
Please, Uhtred.
I know you will not swear to me,

565
00:52:24,558 --> 00:52:27,019
but this child deserves more
than a monastery.

566
00:52:27,102 --> 00:52:32,441
He is a brave and a goodhearted boy,
but he will need guidance.

567
00:52:32,524 --> 00:52:36,737
Protect him and take him to safety.

568
00:52:36,820 --> 00:52:39,073
One aetheling is enough for Winchester.

569
00:52:39,865 --> 00:52:41,158
Bring him within the palace,

570
00:52:41,241 --> 00:52:46,246
it would create a strife
to rival that of Aethelwold.

571
00:52:46,330 --> 00:52:47,414
That is politics.

572
00:52:52,211 --> 00:52:54,421
What would you have me do with him?

573
00:52:54,505 --> 00:52:58,342
Teach him how to be a warrior
and all you know of the Danes.

574
00:52:59,468 --> 00:53:01,512
Teach him of Northumbria.

575
00:53:01,595 --> 00:53:04,598
You have just sworn
you will not fight for Northumbria.

576
00:53:04,682 --> 00:53:08,143
There are ways to take lands
without fighting for them.

577
00:53:08,227 --> 00:53:09,978
Sigtryggr has shown us this.

578
00:53:10,979 --> 00:53:13,148
Northumbria is the last kingdom.

579
00:53:13,232 --> 00:53:15,984
Without it under one King
and under Christ,

580
00:53:16,068 --> 00:53:17,903
there will be no England.

581
00:53:51,854 --> 00:53:55,023
It is hard for a father
to see his daughter go.

582
00:53:55,107 --> 00:53:59,111
But you were right, Father.
Sigtryggr is different.

583
00:53:59,194 --> 00:54:01,196
Perhaps I was not so foolish.

584
00:54:02,448 --> 00:54:04,241
Or someone was guiding you.

585
00:54:05,659 --> 00:54:07,661
The gods like to see me fight.

586
00:54:09,163 --> 00:54:10,497
It is sport to them.

587
00:54:24,052 --> 00:54:26,555
I will return to my church, Father.

588
00:54:30,309 --> 00:54:32,519
I curse myself for my headstrong children.

589
00:54:33,270 --> 00:54:36,899
What can I say? My blood
is the blood of a stubborn bastard.

590
00:54:51,663 --> 00:54:57,669
So, in the reign of King Edward,
peace broke out between Saxon and Dane.

591
00:55:00,506 --> 00:55:06,553
And though it was not for the first time,
there was a sense the truce would last.

592
00:55:08,305 --> 00:55:09,890
But at what cost?

593
00:55:14,436 --> 00:55:17,314
Ambition stalks the Saxon palaces.

594
00:55:19,358 --> 00:55:22,486
In time, the King must choose his heir

595
00:55:22,569 --> 00:55:25,030
and the bonds of blood may be tested.

596
00:55:29,618 --> 00:55:31,161
Brothers may be forn apart...

597
00:55:32,621 --> 00:55:34,998
but a throne cannot stay emply.

598
00:55:36,416 --> 00:55:39,920
I now stand alone
with nothing but my sword.

599
00:55:41,547 --> 00:55:44,132
I failed in securing my birthright.

600
00:55:45,425 --> 00:55:47,719
I have given up the woman I love.

601
00:55:48,512 --> 00:55:50,389
My family are dispersed...

602
00:55:51,139 --> 00:55:53,475
perhaps never fo be reunited...

603
00:55:53,559 --> 00:55:56,645
Scattered far across the Saxon kingdoms.

604
00:56:02,943 --> 00:56:07,698
As a new feud is born,
revenge is certain to grow stronger.

605
00:56:13,787 --> 00:56:16,665
I have sworn to protect a bastard child...

606
00:56:17,875 --> 00:56:22,671
whose path, I fear, is entwined
with that of this great land.

607
00:56:24,131 --> 00:56:28,343
And though I have refused
the service of Saxon Kings,

608
00:56:28,427 --> 00:56:30,971
it may only be a matter of time

609
00:56:31,054 --> 00:56:34,349
before fate draws me back
info their plans.

610
00:56:34,933 --> 00:56:37,477
Destiny is all!

611
00:56:37,501 --> 00:56:39,501
http://hiqve.com/

